s1 = 0\n|club-update    = 18:04, 19 January 2020 (UTC)\n|ntupdate       = \n}}\n'''Javier Andorr\u00e0 Julia''' (born 7 June 1985) is an Andorran international [[association football|footballer]] who plays for the B-team of [[FC Andorra]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\n==Career==\nHe has played for [[FC Andorra]], [[CD Benicarl\u00f3]], [[CF Gimn\u00e1stico Alc\u00e1zar]], [[CD Bin\u00e9far]], [[Inter Club d'Escaldes]] and [[FC Lusitanos]].<ref name = \"NFT\">{{NFT player|pid=11715|accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe made his international debut for [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in 2005.<ref name = \"NFT\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.lapreferente.com/J157961/fc-andorra-b/xavi-andorr%C3%A0.html Xavi Andorr\u00e0] at La Preferente\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Andorra, Xavi}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Andorran footballers]]\n[[Category:Andorra international footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Andorra players]]\n[[Category:CF Gimn\u00e1stico Alc\u00e1zar players]]\n[[Category:CD Bin\u00e9far players]]\n[[Category:Inter Club d'Escaldes players]]\n[[Category:FC Lusitanos players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Andorran expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Andorran expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n\n\n{{Andorra-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2011}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Xavi Andorr\u00e0\n|image          = XaviandInter.jpg\n|image_size     = 300\n|caption        = \n|fullname       = Javier Andorr\u00e0 Julia<ref name = \"NFT\"/>\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1985|6|7|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = \n|height         = 1.83m<ref name = \"NFT\"/>\n|position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|currentclub    = [[FC Andorra|Andorra B]]\n|clubnumber     =\n|years1         = 2004\u20132006\n|clubs1         = [[FC Andorra|Andorra]]\n|caps1          = \n|goals1         = \n|years2         = 2006\u20132007\n|clubs2         = [[CD Benicarl\u00f3|Benicarl\u00f3]]\n|caps2          = \n|goals2         = \n|years3         = 2007\u20132008\n|clubs3         = [[CF Gimn\u00e1stico Alc\u00e1zar|Gimn\u00e1stico Alc\u00e1zar]]\n|caps3          = 29\n|goals3         = 0\n|years4         = 2008\u20132009\n|clubs4         = [[CD Bin\u00e9far|Bin\u00e9far]]\n|caps4          = 9\n|goals4         = 3\n|years5         = 2009\u20132012\n|clubs5         = [[FC Andorra|Andorra]]\n|caps5          = \n|goals5         = \n|years6         = 2012\u20132013\n|clubs6         = [[Inter Club d'Escaldes|IC d'Escaldes]]\n|caps6          = 11\n|goals6         = 3\n|years7         = 2013\u20132014\n|clubs7         = [[FC Andorra|Andorra]]\n|caps7          = 25\n|goals7         = 0\n|years8         = 2014\u20132015\n|clubs8         = [[FC Lusitanos|Lusitanos]]\n|caps8          = 11\n|goals8         = 2\n|years9         = 2015\u20132019\n|clubs9         = [[Inter Club d'Escaldes|IC d'Escaldes]]\n|caps9          = 47\n|goals9         = 12\n|years10        = 2019\u2013\n|clubs10        = [[FC Andorra|Andorra B]]\n|caps10         = 5\n|goals10        = 1\n|nationalyears1 = 2005\u20132013\n|nationalteam1  = [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 24\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n|club-update    = 18:04, 19 January 2020 (UTC)\n|ntupdate       = \n}}\n'''Javier Andorr\u00e0 Julia''' (born 7 June 1985) is an Andorran international [[association football|footballer]] who plays for the B-team of [[FC Andorra]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\n==Career==\nHe has played for [[FC Andorra]], [[CD Benicarl\u00f3]], [[CF Gimn\u00e1stico Alc\u00e1zar]], [[CD Bin\u00e9far]], [[Inter Club d'Escaldes]] and [[FC Lusitanos]].<ref name = \"NFT\">{{NFT player|pid=11715|accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe made his international debut for [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in 2005.<ref name = \"NFT\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.lapreferente.com/J157961/fc-andorra-b/xavi-andorr%C3%A0.html Xavi Andorr\u00e0] at La Preferente\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Andorra, Xavi}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Andorran footballers]]\n[[Category:Andorra international footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Andorra players]]\n[[Category:CF Gimn\u00e1stico Alc\u00e1zar players]]\n[[Category:CD Bin\u00e9far players]]\n[[Category:Inter Club d'Escaldes players]]\n[[Category:FC Lusitanos players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Andorran expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Andorran expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n\n\n{{Andorra-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Andorran footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"Andorran association football player\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xavi_Andorr%C3%A0"}
{"title_page": "Teori Zavascki", "text_new": "{{Expand Portuguese|topic=government|date=January 2017}}\n{{Portuguese name|Albino|Zavascki}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| office1      = [[Supreme Federal Court|Justice of the Supreme Federal Court]]\n| termstart1   = 29 November 2012\n| termend1     = 19 January 2017\n| appointer1   = [[Dilma Rousseff]]\n| predecessor1 = [[Cezar Peluso]]\n| successor1   = [[Alexandre de Moraes]]\n| office2      = [[Superior Court of Justice (Brazil)|Justice of the Superior Court of Justice]]\n| termstart2   = 8 May 2003\n| termend2     = 29 November 2012\n| appointer2   = [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva]]\n| predecessor2 = Jacy Garcia Vieira\n| successor2   = Regina Helena Costa\n| image        = Teori_Zavascki-edit.jpg\n| birth_name   = Teori Albino Zavascki\n| birth_place  = [[Faxinal dos Guedes]], [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]], Brazil\n| birth_date   = {{birth date|1948|8|15|df=y}}\n| death_date   = {{death date and age|2017|1|19|1948|8|15|df=y}}\n| death_place  = [[Paraty]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n| death_cause  = [[Aviation accidents and incidents|Plane crash]]\n| resting_place= Jardim da Paz Cemitery<br>[[Porto Alegre]], [[Rio Grande do Sul]], Brazil\n| occupation   = [[Judge]]\n| nationality  = [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]]\n| alma_mater   = Law School, Federal University of Rio Grande do Sul (UFRGS)\n| spouse       = Maria Helena Marques de Castro {{small|(?&ndash;2013)}}\n| children     = Alexandre Prehn Zavascki <br> Liliana Maria Prehn Zavascki <br> Francisco Prehn Zavascki\n| father       = Severino Zavascki\n| mother       = Pia Maria Fontana Zavascki\n}}\n'''Teori Albino Zavascki''' (15 August 1948 \u2013 19 January 2017) was a [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]] [[judge]] who served as a [[Superior Court of Justice (Brazil)|Minister of the Superior Court of Justice]] from 8 May 2003 until 29 November 2012,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stj.jus.br/web/verCurriculoMinistro?parametro=3&cod_matriculamin=0001124|title=STJ - Ministros Aposentados e Ex-Ministros|publisher=Superior Tribunal de Justi\u00e7a|language=pt-br|accessdate=21 March 2017}}</ref> appointed by President [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva]], and as a [[Supreme Court of Brazil|Minister of the Supreme Federal Court of Brazil]] from 29 November 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stf.jus.br/portal/cms/verNoticiaDetalhe.asp?idConteudo=225207|title=Teori Zavascki toma posse como ministro do STF (Portuguese)|publisher=STF|date=29 December 2012|accessdate= 20 January 2017}}</ref> until his death in 19 January 2017, having been appointed to the position by President [[Dilma Rousseff]]. At the time of his death he was the justice in charge of the trials resulting from [[Operation Car Wash]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-crash-idUSKBN1532WH|title=Plane carrying Brazil Supreme Court judge crashes into sea|date=19 January 2017|publisher=|accessdate=19 January 2017|via=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Langlois|first1=Jill|title=Brazilian Supreme Court justice, who oversaw corruption case, is killed in plane crash|url=http://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-brazil-justice-plane-crash-20170119-story.html|accessdate=20 January 2017|work=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\n\n== Death ==\n\nZavascki was killed in an air disaster in [[Paraty]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]] on 19 January 2017. Official enquiries into the crash began on 20 January<ref>{{cite news|title=Brazil begins probe of plane crash that killed top court justice|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-crash-idUSKBN15429P?il=0|accessdate=20 January 2017|work=Reuters|date=20 January 2017}}</ref> and the [[cockpit voice recorder]] was recovered. Also killed were four other people on board, including the pilot, and {{ILL|Carlos Alberto Fernandes Filgueiras|pt}}, a partner in [[BTG Pactual]], whose president, [[Andr\u00e9 Esteves]], had been arrested in the [[Operation Car Wash]] investigation.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/19/brazil-judge-played-key-role-corruption-investigation-dies-plane/ |title=Brazil judge who played key role in corruption investigation dies in plane crash |agency=Associated Press |publisher=The Telegraph |date=January 19, 2017 |access-date=February 14, 2018}}</ref> More than two hundred politicians and business people were possibly implicated in a [[graft (politics)|graft scheme]] that Zavascki was investigating.<ref>{{cite news|title=Funeral of major graft probe judge killed in plane crash|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-crash-idUSKBN1550K2?il=0|accessdate=21 January 2017|work=Reuters|date=21 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Final Investigation Results ===\nOn 22.01.2018, the [[Aeronautical Accidents Investigation and Prevention Center]] (Centro de Investiga\u00e7\u00e3o e Preven\u00e7\u00e3o de Acidentes Aeron\u00e1uticos, CENIPA) presented their final report. The conclusion was that there was no shortage of kerosene.  Apparently the accident was caused by three major factors:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fab.mil.br/noticias/mostra/31575/SEGURAN%C3%87A%20DE%20VOO%20%E2%80%93%20FAB%20divulga%20resultado%20de%20investiga%C3%A7%C3%A3o%20sobre%20acidente%20com%20aeronave%20PR-SOM|title=FAB divulga resultado de investiga\u00e7\u00e3o sobre acidente com aeronave PR-SOM|date=22 January 2018|accessdate=30 July 2018|publisher=For\u00e7a A\u00e9rea Brasileira}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.potter.net.br/media/rf/pt/PRSOM_POR_VERSION_FINAL.pdf|title= Relat\u00f3rio Final A-013/CENIPA/2017|date=16 January 2018|accessdate=30 July 2018|publisher= CENIPA}}</ref>\n* Bad visual climate conditions. At the time of the accident the horizontal visibility was 1500 meters and the rainfall was 25 mm/h.\n* Cultural practices of the pilots: the investigations found that several pilots who fly in this region rely heavily on their experience and don't follow strict security procedures, including informal practices which inhibit an adequate analysis of the risks involved in this specific landing procedure.\n* Spatial disorientation: as a consequence of the bad visibility, the flight curve executed, the low level above the sea and the stress of the pilot, he probably lost control of the plane.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=Jacy Garcia Vieira}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Superior Court of Justice (Brazil)|Justice of the Superior Court of Justice]]|years=2003\u201312}}\n{{s-aft|after=Regina Helena Costa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Cezar Peluso]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Supreme Federal Court|Justice of the Supreme Federal Court]]|years=2012\u201317}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Alexandre de Moraes]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zavascki, Teori}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Faxinal dos Guedes]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Polish descent]]\n[[Category:Supreme Federal Court of Brazil justices]]\n[[Category:21st-century judges]]\n[[Category:Victims of aviation accidents or incidents in Brazil]]\n\n\n{{Brazil-law-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Expand Portuguese|topic=government|date=January 2017}}\n{{Portuguese name|Albino|Zavascki}}\n{{infobox officeholder\n| office1      = [[Supreme Federal Court|Justice of the Supreme Federal Court]]\n| termstart1   = 29 November 2012\n| termend1     = 19 January 2017\n| appointer1   = [[Dilma Rousseff]]\n| predecessor1 = [[Cezar Peluso]]\n| successor1   = [[Alexandre de Moraes]]\n| office2      = [[Superior Court of Justice (Brazil)|Justice of the Superior Court of Justice]]\n| termstart2   = 8 May 2003\n| termend2     = 29 November 2012\n| appointer2   = [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva]]\n| predecessor2 = Jacy Garcia Vieira\n| successor2   = Regina Helena Costa\n| image        = Teori_Zavascki-edit.jpg\n| birth_name   = Teori Albino Zavascki\n| birth_place  = [[Faxinal dos Guedes]], [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]], Brazil\n| birth_date   = {{birth date|1948|8|15|df=y}}\n| death_date   = {{death date and age|2017|1|19|1948|8|15|df=y}}\n| death_place  = [[Paraty]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil\n| death_cause  = [[Aviation accidents and incidents|Plane crash]]\n| resting_place= Jardim da Paz Cemitery<br>[[Porto Alegre]], [[Rio Grande do Sul]], Brazil\n| occupation   = [[Judge]]\n| nationality  = [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]]\n| alma_mater   = Law School, Federal University of Rio Grande do Sul (UFRGS)\n| spouse       = Maria Helena Marques de Castro {{small|(?&ndash;2013)}}\n| children     = Alexandre Prehn Zavascki <br> Liliana Maria Prehn Zavascki <br> Francisco Prehn Zavascki\n| father       = Severino Zavascki\n| mother       = Pia Maria Fontana Zavascki\n}}\n'''Teori Albino Zavascki''' (15 August 1948 \u2013 19 January 2017) was a [[Brazilian people|Brazilian]] [[judge]] who served as a [[Superior Court of Justice (Brazil)|Minister of the Superior Court of Justice]] from 8 May 2003 until 29 November 2012,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stj.jus.br/web/verCurriculoMinistro?parametro=3&cod_matriculamin=0001124|title=STJ - Ministros Aposentados e Ex-Ministros|publisher=Superior Tribunal de Justi\u00e7a|language=pt-br|accessdate=21 March 2017}}</ref> appointed by President [[Luiz In\u00e1cio Lula da Silva]], and as a [[Supreme Court of Brazil|Minister of the Supreme Federal Court of Brazil]] from 29 November 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stf.jus.br/portal/cms/verNoticiaDetalhe.asp?idConteudo=225207|title=Teori Zavascki toma posse como ministro do STF (Portuguese)|publisher=STF|date=29 December 2012|accessdate= 20 January 2017}}</ref> until his death in 19 January 2017, having been appointed to the position by President [[Dilma Rousseff]]. At the time of his death he was the justice in charge of the trials resulting from [[Operation Car Wash]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-crash-idUSKBN1532WH|title=Plane carrying Brazil Supreme Court judge crashes into sea|date=19 January 2017|publisher=|accessdate=19 January 2017|via=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Langlois|first1=Jill|title=Brazilian Supreme Court justice, who oversaw corruption case, is killed in plane crash|url=http://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-brazil-justice-plane-crash-20170119-story.html|accessdate=20 January 2017|work=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\n\n== Death ==\n\nZavascki was killed in an air disaster in [[Paraty]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]] on 19 January 2017. Official enquiries into the crash began on 20 January<ref>{{cite news|title=Brazil begins probe of plane crash that killed top court justice|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-crash-idUSKBN15429P?il=0|accessdate=20 January 2017|work=Reuters|date=20 January 2017}}</ref> and the [[cockpit voice recorder]] was recovered. Also killed were four other people on board, including the pilot, and {{ILL|Carlos Alberto Fernandes Filgueiras|pt}}, a partner in [[BTG Pactual]], whose president, [[Andr\u00e9 Esteves]], had been arrested in the [[Operation Car Wash]] investigation.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/19/brazil-judge-played-key-role-corruption-investigation-dies-plane/ |title=Brazil judge who played key role in corruption investigation dies in plane crash |agency=Associated Press |publisher=The Telegraph |date=January 19, 2017 |access-date=February 14, 2018}}</ref> More than two hundred politicians and business people were possibly implicated in a [[graft (politics)|graft scheme]] that Zavascki was investigating.<ref>{{cite news|title=Funeral of major graft probe judge killed in plane crash|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brazil-crash-idUSKBN1550K2?il=0|accessdate=21 January 2017|work=Reuters|date=21 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Final Investigation Results ===\nOn 22.01.2018, the [[Aeronautical Accidents Investigation and Prevention Center]] (Centro de Investiga\u00e7\u00e3o e Preven\u00e7\u00e3o de Acidentes Aeron\u00e1uticos, CENIPA) presented their final report. The conclusion was that there was no shortage of kerosene.  Apparently the accident was caused by three major factors:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fab.mil.br/noticias/mostra/31575/SEGURAN%C3%87A%20DE%20VOO%20%E2%80%93%20FAB%20divulga%20resultado%20de%20investiga%C3%A7%C3%A3o%20sobre%20acidente%20com%20aeronave%20PR-SOM|title=FAB divulga resultado de investiga\u00e7\u00e3o sobre acidente com aeronave PR-SOM|date=22 January 2018|accessdate=30 July 2018|publisher=For\u00e7a A\u00e9rea Brasileira}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.potter.net.br/media/rf/pt/PRSOM_POR_VERSION_FINAL.pdf|title= Relat\u00f3rio Final A-013/CENIPA/2017|date=16 January 2018|accessdate=30 July 2018|publisher= CENIPA}}</ref>\n* Bad visual climate conditions. At the time of the accident the horizontal visibility was 1500 meters and the rainfall was 25 mm/h.\n* cultural practices of the pilots: the investigations found that several pilots who fly in this region rely heavily on their experience and don't follow strict security procedures, including informal practices which inhibit an adequate analysis of the risks involved in this specific landing procedure.\n* Spatial disorientation: as a consequence of the bad visibility, the flight curve executed, the low level above the sea and the stress of the pilot, he probably lost control of the plane.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=Jacy Garcia Vieira}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Superior Court of Justice (Brazil)|Justice of the Superior Court of Justice]]|years=2003\u201312}}\n{{s-aft|after=Regina Helena Costa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Cezar Peluso]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Supreme Federal Court|Justice of the Supreme Federal Court]]|years=2012\u201317}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Alexandre de Moraes]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zavascki, Teori}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Faxinal dos Guedes]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Polish descent]]\n[