{"title_page": "Jordi Al\u00e1ez", "text_new": "{{short description|Andorran footballer and beach soccer player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Jordi Al\u00e1ez\n|image          = Andorra national football team - Jordi Al\u00e1ez (001).jpg\n|image_size     = \n|caption        = Al\u00e1ez in 2016\n|fullname       = Jordi Al\u00e1ez Pe\u00f1a\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1998|1|23|df=y}}\n|birth_place    = [[Sant Juli\u00e0 de L\u00f2ria]], Andorra\n|height         = \n|position       = [[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub    = [[FC Santa Coloma]]\n|clubnumber     = 18\n|youthyears1    = \u20132015\n|youthclubs1    = [[FC Andorra]]\n|years1         = 2015\u20132019\n|clubs1         = [[FC Andorra]]\n|caps1          = ?\n|goals1         = ?\n|years2         = 2019\u2013\n|clubs2         = [[FC Santa Coloma]]\n|caps2          = 8\n|goals2         = 2\n|nationalyears1 = 2013\u20132014\n|nationalteam1  = [[Andorra national under-17 football team|Andorra U17]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 6\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n|nationalyears2 = 2015\u2013\n|nationalteam2  = [[Andorra national under-19 football team|Andorra U19]]\n|nationalcaps2  = 8\n|nationalgoals2 = 0\n|nationalyears3 = 2015\u2013\n|nationalteam3  = [[Andorra national under-21 football team|Andorra U21]]\n|nationalcaps3  = 11\n|nationalgoals3 = 2\n|nationalyears4 = 2016\u2013\n|nationalteam4  = [[Andorra national beach soccer team|Andorra (beach soccer)]]\n|nationalcaps4  = 2\n|nationalgoals4 = 0\n|nationalyears5 = 2016\u2013\n|nationalteam5  = [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]]\n|nationalcaps5  = 25\n|nationalgoals5 = 1\n|club-update    = 9 November 2019\n|nationalteam-update = 14 November 2019\n}}\n\n'''Jordi Al\u00e1ez Pe\u00f1a''' (born 23 January 1998) is an [[Andorra]]n [[Association football|footballer]] and [[beach soccer]] player for [[FC Santa Coloma]], the [[Andorra national beach soccer team]] and the [[Andorra national football team|Andorra national team]].<ref name=\"NFT\">{{NFT player|id=64374|accessdate=June 18, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Playing career==\n\n===Club career===\nAl\u00e1ez quickly progressed through the youth ranks of [[FC Andorra]], a club based in [[Andorra]] but playing in the [[Spanish football league system]]. As part of the \"juvenile\" (U18) team, he helped them achieve a near perfect season (25 wins, 3 draws, 1 loss) in 2014\u201315 to achieve promotion to the third-tier.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.elperiodic.ad/noticia/44382/esforc-i-humilitat-les-claus-de-lascens|title=Esfor\u00e7 i humilitat, les claus de l\u2019ascens|first=Albert|last=Canes|publisher=[[El Peri\u00f2dic d'Andorra]]|date=May 29, 2015|accessdate=June 20, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref>  He was called up to the first squad (playing in the fifth-tier [[Primera Catalana]]) before the start of the 2015\u201316 season. He made his debut less than a month after his 18th birthday, replacing [[Alexandre Mart\u00ednez]] in the 79' of a 4-0 home win against [[UA Horta]] on February 14, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lapreferente.com/P1022117/2015-2016/fc-andorra-vs-ua-horta|title=F.C. Andorra 4 - U.A. Horta 0|publisher=La Preferente|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n===International debut===\n\n====Youth====\n\nAl\u00e1ez made his debut for the [[Andorra national under-17 football team|Andorra under-17 national team]] in October 2013, playing all three matches in the [[2014 UEFA European Under-17 Championship qualifying round|2014 Euro U17 qualifiers]] (against [[Serbia national under-17 football team|Serbia]], [[Greece national under-17 football team|Greece]] and [[Estonia national under-17 football team|Estonia]], respectively).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.faf.ad/pnfg/NNws_ShwNewDup?codigo=1005438&cod_primaria=3000301&cod_secundaria=3000301#.V2bdHtIrJdg|title=Convocat\u00f2ria de la selecci\u00f3 sub17 per la fase que tindr\u00e0 lloc a S\u00e8rbia|publisher=[[Andorran Football Federation]]|date=September 26, 2013|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.faf.ad/pnfg/NNws_ShwNewDup?codigo=1005441&cod_primaria=3000316&cod_secundaria=3000316#.V2bcQ9IrJdg|title=La selecci\u00f3 sub17 mereix l'empat contra la favorita Gr\u00e8cia que marca al 79'|publisher=[[Andorran Football Federation]]|date=October 3, 2013|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref> He was 15 years old. He subsequently captained Andorra U17 at the [[2015 UEFA European Under-17 Championship qualifying round|following year's qualifiers]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.faf.ad/pnfg/NNws_ShwNewDup?codigo=1005758&cod_primaria=3000316&cod_secundaria=3000678#.V2bn6NIrJdg|title=Romania nom\u00e9s pot superar a Andorra de penal en la clausura del mini-torneig|publisher=[[Andorran Football Federation]]|date=September 30, 2015|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref> recording one assist in three games as they failed to pass the group stage once again.\n\nHe also appeared in five matches for the [[Andorra national under-19 football team|Andorra national under-19 team]], three times in the [[2015 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification|2015 Euro U19 qualifiers]] in [[Poland]] and twice in the [[2016 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification|2016 Euro 19 qualifiers]] in [[Romania]].\n\nHis debut with the [[Andorra national under-21 football team|Andorra national under-21 team]] was on March 26, 2015, where he played the full 90 minutes in a 1-0 loss to the [[Republic of Ireland national under-21 football team|Republic of Ireland]].\n\n====Senior====\nAl\u00e1ez made his senior international debut for [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] by playing the full 90 minutes of a 0-0 draw in a friendly against [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] on May 26, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://cadenaser.com/emisora/2016/05/27/radio_ser_principat_d_andorra/1464362405_547791.html|title=La selecci\u00f3 andorrana de futbol empata davant d'Azerbaidjan|publisher=[[Cadena SER]]|date=March 26, 2016|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.diariandorra.ad/noticies/esports/2016/05/27/una_solida_andorra_empata_sense_gols_contra_azerbaidjan_102555_1128.html|title=Una s\u00f2lida Andorra empata sense gols contra l'Azerbaidjan|publisher=[[Diari d'Andorra]]|date=May 27, 2016|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref> Al\u00e1ez was among the four \"fresh faces\" with no previous senior international experience that manager [[Koldo|Koldo \u00c1lvarez]] decided to include in the 18-man squad the day before the match, showing great confidence in the young players.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.diariandorra.ad/noticies/esports/2016/05/25/koldo_obre_porta_als_joves_alaez_martinez_matos_102466_1128.html|title=Koldo obre la porta als joves Al\u00e1ez, Mart\u00ednez i Matos|first=Sergi|last=Cano|publisher=[[Diari d'Andorra]]|date=May 26, 2016|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.andorradifusio.ad/Esports/koldo-alvarez-aposta-per-les-cares-noves-a-lamistos-contra-lazerbaidjan|title=Koldo \u00c1lvarez aposta per les cares noves a l'amist\u00f3s contra l'Azerbaidjan|publisher=Andorra Difusi\u00f3|date=May 19, 2016|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref> He earned his second cap a week later, coming on as a 65' substitute for Alexandre Mart\u00ednez during a 2-0 loss to [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]] in [[Tallinn]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.faf.ad/pnfg/NNws_ShwNewDup?codigo=1006728&cod_primaria=3000301&cod_secundaria=3000301#.V2d0EtIrJdg|title=Derrota ajustada de la Selecci\u00f3 a Tallinn en el centenari d'Ilde Lima (2-0)|publisher=[[Andorran Football Federation]]|date=June 1, 2016|accessdate=June 19, 2016|language=Catalan}}</ref>\n\n==National team statistics==\n{{updated|match played 19 November 2018}}<ref name=NFT/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=3 | [[Andorra national football team|Andorra national tea